WEBVTT

00:01.335 --> 00:01.502
.

00:01.535 --> 00:02.370
- Previously on
"Good Girls"...

00:03.171 --> 00:05.073
- Are we going
to lose this house?

00:05.106 --> 00:06.374
- No.
I mean, I don't know.

00:06.407 --> 00:08.276
- Nancy and I are
suing you for custody.

00:08.309 --> 00:09.610
- Can I have lunch money?

00:09.643 --> 00:12.213
- Those kids take it again?
Douchebags.

00:12.246 --> 00:13.414
- The drug that
you're talking about?

00:13.447 --> 00:15.116
Ten grand a month,
out of pocket.

00:15.149 --> 00:17.385
And I'm guessing
that may not be an option.

00:17.418 --> 00:18.752
- How much is in the vault?

00:18.786 --> 00:20.354
- 30 grand,
give or take.

00:20.388 --> 00:22.256
- So when do you wanna do this?

00:22.290 --> 00:25.126
- Ladies and gentlemen,
this is a robbery.

00:25.159 --> 00:27.661
- You know how fast
they're gonna lock you up?

00:27.695 --> 00:29.263
- [screams]
[glass clinks]

00:29.297 --> 00:30.431
- [pants]

00:30.464 --> 00:33.667
- He wants us to pick something
up for him in Canada.

00:33.701 --> 00:37.338
It's wrapping paper.
It's just wrapping paper.

00:37.371 --> 00:38.739
I just need to know
we're good.

00:38.772 --> 00:40.541
I'm gonna need
to hear you say it.

00:40.574 --> 00:41.775
- We're good.

00:41.809 --> 00:44.445
- Here's to going
back to normal life.

00:44.478 --> 00:45.679
- L'chaim to that.

00:45.713 --> 00:49.117
- So what'd you
wanna talk to me about?

00:50.551 --> 00:52.853
- Mom, mom, mom.

00:52.886 --> 00:54.622
It's not fair.

00:54.655 --> 00:56.557
For Tommy's birthday, we all
went out to a Pistons game.

00:56.590 --> 00:59.560
We got box seats, and his mom
bought us all jerseys.

00:59.593 --> 01:01.862
And then--
and then after that,

01:01.895 --> 01:03.564
they rented a hotel
with room service.

01:03.597 --> 01:06.400
- Yeah, and now Tommy's mom
can't afford college.

01:06.434 --> 01:08.169
- Well, I want
a birthday party.

01:08.202 --> 01:10.304
- How about a sleepover?
- With a chocolate fountain.

01:10.338 --> 01:12.273
- You could nuke a Hershey bar.
- Mama?

01:12.306 --> 01:13.707
- This is the worst
birthday ever.

01:13.741 --> 01:15.376
- Mama?

01:15.409 --> 01:16.644
- Listen, well, we can't just
afford a really big,

01:16.677 --> 01:18.146
fancy party right now.
We just can't.

01:18.179 --> 01:19.547
- Mama?

01:19.580 --> 01:21.715
- But I promise you,
I'm gonna make it special.

01:21.749 --> 01:22.883
I promise you, okay.

01:22.916 --> 01:25.319
- Mama!
- What is it?

01:25.353 --> 01:27.655
- Who's the man?
- What man?

01:27.688 --> 01:29.823
- The man on my bed.

01:29.857 --> 01:32.826
[upbeat music]

01:32.860 --> 01:34.562
*

01:34.595 --> 01:37.731
- No, no, stay--
stay here, stay here.

01:37.765 --> 01:45.139
*

01:54.682 --> 02:01.722
*

02:03.557 --> 02:05.926
*

02:05.959 --> 02:10.498
Hey, you wanna go swimming
at your dad's?

02:10.531 --> 02:11.499
- Yay!

02:11.532 --> 02:12.666
- Yay.

02:12.700 --> 02:16.804
*

02:16.837 --> 02:19.673
[indistinct chatter]

02:24.612 --> 02:26.514
- Yo, Ruby.

02:26.547 --> 02:29.217
- [sighs] That's my name,
don't wear it out.

02:29.250 --> 02:31.585
- How does one become
a waitress here?

02:31.619 --> 02:32.920
- Excuse me?

02:32.953 --> 02:34.688
- Like, what college
has the best program?

02:34.722 --> 02:36.757
[chuckling]

02:36.790 --> 02:38.259
- I'll check if we're hiring.

02:38.292 --> 02:39.293
- Do you have
to buy the uniform?

02:39.327 --> 02:40.761
'Cause that's some--

02:40.794 --> 02:42.730
I mean, that's some high
quality polyester right there.

02:42.763 --> 02:45.266
I mean, that would set me back,
what--ten bucks?

02:45.299 --> 02:47.635
- Ah [chuckles].

02:49.437 --> 02:51.405
- Just go make him
another one.

02:51.439 --> 02:54.242
He can't eat this now.

02:54.275 --> 02:56.877
Come on,
chop-chop, Ruby.

02:56.910 --> 03:00.214
- Is there a problem,
milkshake?

03:00.248 --> 03:01.482
- What'd you call me?

03:01.515 --> 03:03.551
- It's a trick I use
to remember orders.

03:03.584 --> 03:07.255
Since I didn't go to college
and my memory's not so great.

03:07.288 --> 03:09.323
You always order
that milkshake,

03:09.357 --> 03:10.558
which you never finish,

03:10.591 --> 03:12.560
so you can be sure
to leave my tip

03:12.593 --> 03:14.695
in the bottom
of your nasty ass cup.

03:14.728 --> 03:17.265
My two percent tip.

03:17.298 --> 03:18.999
Three, if you're
feeling generous.

03:19.032 --> 03:21.502
*

03:21.535 --> 03:24.004
It's not the money that I mind.

03:24.037 --> 03:26.640
I mean, if you can't afford it,
I get it.

03:26.674 --> 03:28.376
I feel for you.

03:28.409 --> 03:31.712
But please, let me know if
there's anything that I can do

03:31.745 --> 03:35.983
to make your experience here
more delightful.

03:36.016 --> 03:38.419
No? Well, then,
I'd appreciate it

03:38.452 --> 03:42.423
if you left your
85 cents on the table,

03:42.456 --> 03:45.659
and not in your shake today.

03:45.693 --> 03:48.796
Cool?
Okay.

03:48.829 --> 03:51.765
*

03:51.799 --> 03:55.769
All right, sweetie, enjoy.

03:55.803 --> 03:58.272
*

03:58.306 --> 04:02.343
- Ah!
[shrieks]

04:02.376 --> 04:05.513
- Oh, that might be hot.

04:05.546 --> 04:09.483
- Ruby, get some ice.
- [whimpers]

04:09.517 --> 04:13.053
- All right, the Marks Express
is leaving, choo-choo--ow!

04:13.086 --> 04:14.755
Zipper.

04:14.788 --> 04:16.490
What? What're you doing?
We--we're gonna be late.

04:16.524 --> 04:17.925
- I hate everything.

04:17.958 --> 04:20.361
- Excuse me?
I just got you these.

04:20.394 --> 04:22.496
You told me they were "lit AF."

04:22.530 --> 04:24.632
- They're too big.
They fall down.

04:24.665 --> 04:26.700
- These are not too big.
No way.

04:26.734 --> 04:29.770
I mean, you'd have
to really yank on them.

04:29.803 --> 04:32.005
Hey, why are you so worried
about your pants falling down?

04:32.039 --> 04:34.342
- I'm not.

04:34.375 --> 04:36.610
- Hey, what--what's going on?
Tell me.

04:36.644 --> 04:39.747
- No.

04:39.780 --> 04:42.082
- Sadie, talk to me.

04:42.115 --> 04:44.318
- No.

04:44.352 --> 04:47.321
[calm music]

04:47.355 --> 04:49.757
*

04:49.790 --> 04:51.725
- Are people, like,

04:51.759 --> 04:55.062
pulling your pants down?

04:55.095 --> 04:57.765
- They wanna know what I am.

04:57.798 --> 05:04.838
*

05:05.706 --> 05:08.376
- So no big deal,
we'll buy you some belts.

05:08.409 --> 05:09.977
Maybe something pink,
and pretty,

05:10.010 --> 05:12.346
and girly, and sparkly, and--
alright, all right, all right.

05:12.380 --> 05:13.781
Not the money maker.

05:13.814 --> 05:14.815
Not the money maker.

05:14.848 --> 05:16.617
Just hurry up,
put something on.

05:16.650 --> 05:18.552
I don't care what it is.
[call phone vibrates]

05:18.586 --> 05:22.523
Be outside in two minutes
or you're dead, I mean it.

05:22.556 --> 05:24.091
- [whispering] Will you
tell us what's going on?

05:24.124 --> 05:27.528
This is freaking me out.

05:27.561 --> 05:28.829
- [whispering]
Oh, my God.

05:28.862 --> 05:30.498
- Who is that?
- I don't know.

05:30.531 --> 05:32.433
- What do you mean
you don't know?

05:32.466 --> 05:33.501
- I mean, I came back
from the grocery store

05:33.534 --> 05:34.968
and he was
just there.

05:35.002 --> 05:39.039
And, I mean, I'm assuming
he's, like, an associate

05:39.072 --> 05:40.608
of the gangbanger.

05:40.641 --> 05:42.476
- Come on, I thought
we were done with that.

05:42.510 --> 05:43.577
- Yeah, what the hell?

05:43.611 --> 05:45.846
- Okay, okay, we were.

05:45.879 --> 05:47.848
And then...

05:47.881 --> 05:49.617
God, this sounds so crazy
even saying it--

05:49.650 --> 05:50.784
- Spit it out.
[snaps fingers]

05:50.818 --> 05:53.454
- I--I--

05:53.487 --> 05:57.124
I offered to do another job.

05:57.157 --> 05:59.092
- Uh--

05:59.126 --> 06:00.461
- You asked for this?

06:00.494 --> 06:01.762
- [guffaws]

06:01.795 --> 06:02.863
- It's not like
we don't need the money.

06:02.896 --> 06:04.164
We all still need the money.

06:04.197 --> 06:07.100
- [snorts]
- So you asked for this?

06:07.134 --> 06:08.569
- No, well, not this.

06:08.602 --> 06:09.570
- [laughs]
- Shh.

06:09.603 --> 06:10.771
- I'm sorry.
[chuckles]

06:10.804 --> 06:12.940
I just can't believe
it's you and not me.

06:12.973 --> 06:14.107
Come on, it's crazy.

06:14.141 --> 06:15.609
- Look, I just--I just said

06:15.643 --> 06:17.144
that we would possibly,

06:17.177 --> 06:20.481
if the circumstances
were right,

06:20.514 --> 06:22.616
pick up another load
of the fake cash.

06:22.650 --> 06:24.752
- You volunteered us?

06:24.785 --> 06:26.987
- It's not drugs.
It's paper.

06:27.020 --> 06:29.022
I mean, it's literally paper.

06:29.056 --> 06:31.459
- You can't sign people up
for criminal activity

06:31.492 --> 06:32.793
like it's a bake sale.

06:32.826 --> 06:34.595
- Noted, but can you
just help me

06:34.628 --> 06:35.963
get this person out of
my house right now?

06:35.996 --> 06:37.197
- Oh, you want some help now?

06:37.230 --> 06:39.166
I'm sorry, why don't you
call your BFF,

06:39.199 --> 06:40.868
the other gangbanger?

06:40.901 --> 06:43.170
- He's not my BFF.

06:43.203 --> 06:45.005
I don't even know
that guy's name.

06:45.038 --> 06:46.173
- No, but I bet--

06:46.206 --> 06:48.509
I bet he does, right?

06:48.542 --> 06:50.978
Maybe I can, uh...

06:51.011 --> 06:53.814
Okay, I guess I'll do it.
- Yeah, mm-hmm, I'm not.

06:55.683 --> 06:57.518
- Just watch my back, okay?
Please.

06:57.551 --> 06:59.119
- Just be careful.

06:59.152 --> 07:02.122
[foreboding music]

07:02.155 --> 07:05.926
*

07:05.959 --> 07:08.962
- I'm sorry, I'm sorry.

07:08.996 --> 07:10.130
- [stammers]

07:10.163 --> 07:12.065
- Sorry, sorry, sorry.

07:12.099 --> 07:15.703
Oh, God, okay.
Well, this is not a phone.

07:15.736 --> 07:17.705
Just--just,
t--take this, take it.

07:17.738 --> 07:20.974
Just take it.
- Oh, my--

07:21.008 --> 07:23.176
*

07:23.210 --> 07:26.547
- Okay.

07:26.580 --> 07:31.552
*

07:31.585 --> 07:33.587
Ugh.
Okay.

07:33.621 --> 07:34.888
I have it,
I have it.

07:34.922 --> 07:36.990
- What's the last number
he called?

07:37.024 --> 07:38.692
- Papa John's.

07:38.726 --> 07:40.694
- The last person, Annie.

07:40.728 --> 07:44.965
- "Mom," "Mom,"
"Mom," "Mom," "Mom..."

07:44.998 --> 07:46.934
- Oh, my God, why didn't
he just go to his mom's?

07:46.967 --> 07:49.803
- "Mom," "Mom," "Mom..."
- I know, seriously.

07:49.837 --> 07:52.239
- "Mom" and...

07:52.272 --> 07:56.577
"Rio."

07:56.610 --> 07:59.112
- That is not what I meant when
I said we'd do another job.

07:59.146 --> 08:00.614
Who is that guy?

08:00.648 --> 08:01.715
- He works for me.

08:01.749 --> 08:03.651
- Do--does he wash the money?

08:03.684 --> 08:05.986
- Regardless, there's been
a miscommunication.

08:06.019 --> 08:08.522
- Oh, so you think you can pick
and choose what you wanna do

08:08.556 --> 08:09.957
and when you wanna do it?

08:09.990 --> 08:11.759
- She thought it would be
like driving for Uber.

08:11.792 --> 08:13.226
- Who's at fault
is not important.

08:13.260 --> 08:16.697
We are not qualified to take
care of a gunshot victim.

08:16.730 --> 08:21.134
I mean, your friend needs
professional medical attention.

08:21.168 --> 08:22.870
You're shaking your head.
Why are you shaking your head?

08:22.903 --> 08:24.137
- 'Cause that kid
ain't going to no hospital.

08:24.171 --> 08:25.606
- Why not?

08:25.639 --> 08:26.874
- 'Cause there's people
looking for him.

08:26.907 --> 08:29.009
- What if those people
show up here?

08:29.042 --> 08:30.210
- Trust me, ain't nobody
gonna shoot up

08:30.243 --> 08:32.546
Beaver Cleaver's house.

08:32.580 --> 08:34.748
[upbeat pop music]

08:34.782 --> 08:37.585
- No, I'm sorry,
that is not gonna work.

08:37.618 --> 08:39.887
- No?

08:39.920 --> 08:41.889
- I--[sighs]

08:41.922 --> 08:43.891
- Oh.
Mm.

08:43.924 --> 08:46.627
*

08:46.660 --> 08:49.997
- I have children.

08:50.030 --> 08:53.667
- * Looking like a zombie,
animal, animal *

08:53.701 --> 08:55.969
* Hey, get out my way

08:56.003 --> 08:57.771
- He's up there in
my daughter's bed.

08:57.805 --> 08:59.573
I'm never gonna get
that blood out.

08:59.607 --> 09:02.042
- I mean, she could sleep
on the floor.

09:02.075 --> 09:03.644
Kids love that stuff.

09:03.677 --> 09:06.213
- I'm pretty sure it'll cover
a new mattress.

09:06.246 --> 09:08.949
- * Don't save me

09:08.982 --> 09:11.785
*

09:11.819 --> 09:15.188
- So, would we get
that money now, or...?

09:15.222 --> 09:16.657
- When I pick him up.

09:16.690 --> 09:19.059
- When's that?
- When I pick him up.

09:19.092 --> 09:21.128
- Sounds fair.

09:21.161 --> 09:24.765
- So, we got a deal, ladies?

09:24.798 --> 09:28.135
Or what?
- [exhales deeply]

09:28.168 --> 09:30.971
- * Don't save me,
don't save me *

09:33.173 --> 09:33.340
.

09:33.373 --> 09:34.141
[telephone rings,
indistinct chatter]

09:35.876 --> 09:38.245
[muffled speech]
- Mr. Petersen.

09:38.278 --> 09:40.047
[fully audible]
Mr. Petersen.

09:40.080 --> 09:43.651
Agent Turner
will see you now.

09:43.684 --> 09:45.052
- [exhales]

09:45.085 --> 09:47.788
- What happened after
they crossed the border?

09:47.821 --> 09:49.690
- Wish I knew.

09:49.723 --> 09:51.124
I lost visual.

09:51.158 --> 09:53.193
- Mm.

09:55.362 --> 09:56.664
Gummy?

09:56.697 --> 09:59.166
- Yeah.
- Please.

09:59.199 --> 10:01.802
So, just so I got this,
okay, these women,

10:01.835 --> 10:03.704
they took a car--
- Stole.

10:03.737 --> 10:04.805
I mean, they stole a car.

10:04.838 --> 10:07.340
- And drove it over the border.

10:07.374 --> 10:10.911
- What's your gut say?

10:10.944 --> 10:12.813
- I mean, jeez.

10:12.846 --> 10:14.047
Any number of things.

10:14.081 --> 10:16.149
International drug ring.
Human trafficking.

10:16.183 --> 10:18.886
Sleeper cell.
- Homegrown jihadis.

10:18.919 --> 10:22.122
- I'm not ready
to rule out anything.

10:26.293 --> 10:28.328
- Mmm.

10:31.298 --> 10:33.300
- And the one
that works with you?

10:33.333 --> 10:35.836
- Oh, I mean, if anyone
got radicalized, it's her.

10:35.869 --> 10:36.937
[laughs]
- I bet.

10:36.970 --> 10:39.973
What's her name?
- Annie.

10:40.007 --> 10:43.010
- My Annie was a Paula.
She lived in my dorm.

10:43.043 --> 10:46.413
- What?
- Ah, we both loved Hoobastank.

10:46.446 --> 10:48.048
- Wait, hold on a second--
- But it didn't matter.

10:48.081 --> 10:49.717
I was stuck I the friend zone.
- No.

10:49.750 --> 10:51.151
- Just like you, right?
- No, that's not it at all,

10:51.184 --> 10:52.753
actually.
- You sure about that, Leslie?

10:52.786 --> 10:56.423
- They have committed crimes.
I can prove it.

10:56.456 --> 10:57.891
Well, I can't prove it.

10:57.925 --> 11:00.160
But I can.

11:00.193 --> 11:01.394
But I can't.

11:01.428 --> 11:04.164
I mean, I wa--I want to.
- I'll tell you what.

11:04.197 --> 11:06.166
I'll do a little digging, okay?

11:06.199 --> 11:08.001
But you gotta do
something for me too.

11:08.035 --> 11:09.369
- Name it.

11:09.402 --> 11:12.472
- Go to O'Brien's.
You know the bar on Birmingham?

11:12.505 --> 11:14.441
Have a couple of cocktails,

11:14.474 --> 11:18.145
and find yourself a nice girl.

11:18.178 --> 11:22.015
Preferably one
that's interested in you.

11:22.049 --> 11:23.183
- And you know
what they call it?

11:23.216 --> 11:25.152
- What?
- A sizzling skillet.

11:25.185 --> 11:27.387
It says sizzling right there
in the menu.

11:27.420 --> 11:28.521
What does that tell you?

11:28.555 --> 11:32.159
- Uh, that it might be hot?
- That it might be hot.

11:32.192 --> 11:34.995
- Might not wanna touch that.
- You think?

11:35.028 --> 11:36.429
And now they're threatening
to lawyer up.

11:36.463 --> 11:38.065
- What?

11:38.098 --> 11:41.501
What does Tony say?
- That I have to apologize.

11:41.534 --> 11:43.804
- Well, all right, then.

11:43.837 --> 11:45.338
- Why should I apologize?

11:45.372 --> 11:48.141
Because I didn't tell
that idiot that the boiling,

11:48.175 --> 11:50.443
bubbling, sizzling platter
in front of him

11:50.477 --> 11:52.312
might be hot?

11:52.345 --> 11:54.414
What's next, We start warning
people that their ice cream

11:54.447 --> 11:56.016
might have a bit
of a chill on it?

11:56.049 --> 11:57.918
Look out.
- Uh.

11:57.951 --> 12:00.420
You--you wanna know why?
- Yeah, why?

12:00.453 --> 12:03.023
- Oh, you--okay.

12:03.056 --> 12:05.325
Come on, come here.
Come here for a second.

12:05.358 --> 12:06.794
Come here.

12:06.827 --> 12:08.061
[tender music]

12:08.095 --> 12:09.529
[giggling]

12:09.562 --> 12:11.198
These little people.

12:11.231 --> 12:13.466
That's why you go back
in there and you suck it up.

12:13.500 --> 12:15.202
Think we're gonna have to put
next month's meds

12:15.235 --> 12:18.471
on four different
credit cards.

12:18.505 --> 12:20.040
- I know.

12:20.073 --> 12:24.344
- And even then,
we might not make it.

12:24.377 --> 12:26.814
- Stan, you should see
these kids.

12:26.847 --> 12:29.182
They come in there.

12:29.216 --> 12:31.484
They're so rude
and disrespectful

12:31.518 --> 12:33.954
and act like they're better
than everyone else.

12:33.987 --> 12:36.489
- Uh, you know I get
called Paul Blart, like,

12:36.523 --> 12:38.491
every single day, right?

12:38.525 --> 12:40.527
Paul Blart.
Mall cop.

12:40.560 --> 12:43.563
Where's your Segway?

12:43.596 --> 12:45.966
Now, but I take it,

12:45.999 --> 12:47.534
because at the end of the day,

12:47.567 --> 12:49.369
I got this to come home to.

12:49.402 --> 12:52.572
For them--um--you do
what you gotta do.

12:52.605 --> 12:54.842
*

12:54.875 --> 12:56.209
- Babe.
- Mm-hmm?

12:56.243 --> 13:00.013
- [sighs]
Chill out with the cayenne.

13:00.047 --> 13:01.849
- That's too hot?
- It's spicy.

13:01.882 --> 13:04.384
- Damn it.

